text: Leninskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) in Mishkinsky Selsoviet, Mishkinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 306 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 9 km from Mishkino. == References == Category:Rural localities in Mishkinsky District
title: Leninskoye, Mishkinsky District, Republic of Bashkortostan
